weight: 190 lbs.
born: July 11, 1976
acquired: Traded from Toronto for Travis Green, Robert Reichel and Craig Mills

The 6-foot-1, 190 pound Markov played 59 games for Toronto last season, recording 3-13-16 and 34 penalty minutes (PIM). Markov finished the season with a plus-6 rating. Despite missing 23 games (February 1 to March 24) with a back injury, Markov set career highs in assists (13) and points (16). He returned to action on March 24 and played in the Maple Leafs' final 7 regular season games and in all 11 playoff games.

During the 1999-2000 season, the 24-year-old native of Moscow, USSR played in a career high 59 games with Toronto, collecting 10 assists and 28 PIM. Markov finished the season with a plus-13 rating and went on to play 12 playoff games for Toronto (3 assists, 10 PIM). In 1998-99, he recorded 4-8-12 and 47 PIM with the Maple Leafs. His 4 goals and 47 penalty minutes were career highs. He finished the season with a plus-5 rating.
